<text top="55" left="90" width="103" height="13" font="1">Security Council</text>
<text top="55" left="735" width="93" height="13" font="1">3941st meeting</text>
<text top="73" left="90" width="93" height="14" font="1">Fifty-third year</text>
<text top="73" left="717" width="111" height="14" font="1">6 November 1998</text>
<text top="109" left="122" width="327" height="14" font="1">and Normalization of Living Conditions in the War-</text>
<text top="127" left="122" width="48" height="14" font="1">affected</text>
<text top="127" left="184" width="49" height="14" font="1">Regions</text>
<text top="127" left="248" width="12" height="14" font="1">of</text>
<text top="127" left="275" width="18" height="14" font="1">the</text>
<text top="127" left="308" width="54" height="14" font="1">Republic</text>
<text top="127" left="377" width="12" height="14" font="1">of</text>
<text top="127" left="404" width="44" height="14" font="1">Croatia</text>
<text top="145" left="122" width="83" height="14" font="1">(S/1997/772).</text>
<text top="181" left="153" width="295" height="14" font="1">"The Security Council expresses its full support</text>
<text top="199" left="122" width="327" height="14" font="1">for the OSCE, which has now assumed the role of the</text>
<text top="217" left="122" width="327" height="14" font="1">United Nations support group, and looks forward to</text>
<text top="235" left="122" width="327" height="14" font="1">being kept informed, whenever necessary, of relevant</text>
<text top="253" left="122" width="289" height="14" font="1">developments in the Danube region of Croatia.</text>
<text top="289" left="153" width="30" height="14" font="1">"The</text>
<text top="289" left="197" width="50" height="14" font="1">Security</text>
<text top="289" left="260" width="48" height="14" font="1">Council</text>
<text top="289" left="321" width="57" height="14" font="1">expresses</text>
<text top="289" left="392" width="14" height="14" font="1">its</text>
<text top="289" left="420" width="28" height="14" font="1">deep</text>
<text top="307" left="122" width="327" height="14" font="1">appreciation to all the men and women who</text>
<text top="109" left="512" width="316" height="14" font="1">participated in the United Nations peacekeeping</text>
<text top="127" left="512" width="316" height="14" font="1">operations in the Danube region of Croatia. Their</text>
<text top="145" left="512" width="316" height="14" font="1">dedication and perseverance made a significant</text>
<text top="163" left="512" width="194" height="14" font="1">contribution to regional peace."</text>
<text top="199" left="512" width="316" height="14" font="1">This statement will be issued as a document of the</text>
<text top="217" left="481" width="325" height="14" font="1">Security Council under the symbol S/PRST/1998/32.</text>
<text top="253" left="512" width="316" height="14" font="1">The Security Council has thus concluded the present</text>
<text top="271" left="481" width="317" height="14" font="1">stage of its consideration of the item on its agenda.</text>
<text top="308" left="512" width="166" height="14" font="5"><i>The meeting rose at 6 p.m.</i></text>
<text top="1084" left="821" width="8" height="14" font="1">3</text>
</page>
